President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 30 to May 6, 2017, as Small Business Week in the United States. The proclamation celebrates the contributions of small business owners to the economy and emphasizes the importance of removing government barriers to their success. Small businesses employ almost 58 million Americans, accounting for about 50 percent of all private-sector jobs in the country. The proclamation also highlights the need for tax reform and favorable trade deals to support small businesses. Overall, the proclamation aims to foster the conditions that enable small businesses to prosper and thrive.